==English==

===Etymology===
from Greek ''[[φιλοσοφία]]'': ''[[φιλοσ]]'' (''philos'') = love + ''[[σοφία]]'' (''sophia'') = wisdom

===Noun===
'''philosophy'''  {{uncountable}}
 
# An academic discipline that is, generally, divided into five major subtopics:  [[Logic]]; [[Metaphysics]]; [[Epistemology]]; [[Ethics]]; and [[Esthetics]]
# A comprehensive system of belief
# A view or outlook of some other domain (e.g. a philosophy of government or a philosophy of education)
# A general principle (usually moral)

